{
  "texts": [
    "It is used to determine the prominence of various spectral peaks.",
    "A higher contrast value suggests sharper spectral peaks, implying different sound components 36.",
    "Spectral Bandwidth: The spectral bandwidth measures the spectral content's width and the audio signal's frequency spread.",
    "While a low value indicates a lower concentration of frequencies, a high value denotes a wide distribution of frequencies 37.",
    "Chroma STFT: The harmonic content of the audio is represented by the chroma Short-Time Fourier Transform (STFT)."
  ]
